Interface ICCalculatorBase.Errors

public static interface ICCalculatorBase.Errors

Contains constants for every error that can happen in an ICCalculatorBase

Since:
1.0
Version:
1.0

Field Summary
static int EVIL_ERROR
          There was an error so bad that an exception was thrown, please email Ean Lombardo
static int INVALID_VARIABLE_NAME
          The variable name given is invalid, not all characters are allowed in variable and function names see VALID_LETTERS for a string of all allowed characters
static int NO_ERROR
          There wasn't an error
static int PARAMETER_MISMATCH
          There were too many or not enough parameters for this function, such as cos(1,2) the cos function only takes one parameter
static int PARENTHESIS_MISMATCH
          There weren't enough parenthesis to evaluate the function, such as 1+(2/4)+6) there should be another ( somewhere
static int SYNTAX_ERROR
          There was an error in syntax, such that the expression was not written correctly to the extent that it could not be run
static int TYPE_MISMATCH
          There was a type mismatch, a function need something different than what you gave it such as derive(x^2,2,3) the 2 should be a variable name, but in that case it is a number
static int UNKOWN_ERROR
          Something happened somewhere that caused an error for some unknown reason
